---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import ScrollReveal from "../../components/react/ScrollReveal.tsx";
---

<BaseLayout title="Journey Management Redesign — Chetan Kummari">
  <main id="main" class="bg-bg-primary min-h-screen py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">

      <!-- Back Link -->
      <a href="/#work" class="text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors text-sm">
        &larr; Back
      </a>

      <!-- Hero -->
      <ScrollReveal client:visible>
        <header class="mt-12 mb-16">
          <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-text-primary mb-4">
            Journey Management Redesign
          </h1>
          <p class="text-lg text-text-secondary italic mb-8">
            Turning a data-heavy logistics screen into an actionable system
          </p>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-x-8 gap-y-2 text-sm text-text-secondary">
            <span><span class="text-text-tertiary">Role:</span> Senior Product Designer</span>
            <span><span class="text-text-tertiary">Company:</span> Freight Tiger</span>
            <span><span class="text-text-tertiary">Timeline:</span> 2024</span>
          </div>
        </header>
      </ScrollReveal>

      <!-- Overview -->
      <ScrollReveal client:visible>
        <section>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-text-primary mt-16 mb-6">Overview</h3>
          <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
            Journeys are the core unit of execution in logistics. The "My Journeys" screen had become a data dump over time — too many columns, mixed signals, no clear priority. Users could see data but had no way to act on it meaningfully.
          </p>
        </section>
      </ScrollReveal>

      <!-- Problem -->
      <ScrollReveal client:visible>
        <section>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-text-primary mt-16 mb-6">Problem</h3>
          <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-6">
            The screen was trying to be four things at once: a tracking dashboard, a reporting table, a notification system, and an action interface. It failed at all four.
          </p>
          <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">Key issues:</p>
          <ol class="list-decimal list-inside text-text-secondary space-y-2">
            <li><strong class="text-text-primary">No clear mental model</strong> — What does "complete" versus "achieved" actually mean?</li>
            <li><strong class="text-text-primary">High cognitive load</strong> — Too many columns, too much information competing for attention.</li>
            <li><strong class="text-text-primary">No actionability</strong> — The screen couldn't answer "What needs attention now?"</li>
            <li><strong class="text-text-primary">Inconsistent states</strong> — Journey states were not aligned across systems.</li>
          </ol>
        </section>
      </ScrollReveal>

      <!-- Insight -->
      <ScrollReveal client:visible>
        <section>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-text-primary mt-16 mb-6">Insight</h3>
          <blockquote class="border-l-2 border-border-subtle pl-6 italic text-text-secondary">
            The problem was not "table design." It was this: the system does not know what a journey means. Without clear states, transitions, and priorities, the UI will always become messy.
          </blockquote>
        </section>
      </ScrollReveal>

      <!-- Solution -->
      <ScrollReveal client:visible>
        <section>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-text-primary mt-16 mb-6">Solution — Three Principles</h3>

          <h4 class="text-lg font-medium text-text-primary mt-8 mb-3">Principle 1: Define a clear journey lifecycle</h4>
          <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
            We standardized journey states into a coherent lifecycle:
          </p>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 text-text-secondary text-sm mb-4">
            <span class="bg-bg-card border border-border-subtle rounded px-3 py-1">En route to loading</span>
            <span class="text-text-tertiary">&rarr;</span>
            <span class="bg-bg-card border border-border-subtle rounded px-3 py-1">At loading</span>
            <span class="text-text-tertiary">&rarr;</span>
            <span class="bg-bg-card border border-border-subtle rounded px-3 py-1">In transit</span>
            <span class="text-text-tertiary">&rarr;</span>
            <span class="bg-bg-card border border-border-subtle rounded px-3 py-1">At destination</span>
            <span class="text-text-tertiary">&rarr;</span>
            <span class="bg-bg-card border border-border-subtle rounded px-3 py-1">Return</span>
            <span class="text-text-tertiary">&rarr;</span>
            <span class="bg-bg-card border border-border-subtle rounded px-3 py-1">Completed</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
            We also introduced an "Achieved" state — inferred rather than confirmed by data, exposing the system's level of confidence to the user.
          </p>

          <h4 class="text-lg font-medium text-text-primary mt-8 mb-3">Principle 2: Action-first, not data-first</h4>
          <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
            Instead of showing everything at once, show what matters now. Actionable filters, clear status signals, and reduced noise help users focus on what requires their attention.
          </p>

          <h4 class="text-lg font-medium text-text-primary mt-8 mb-3">Principle 3: Separate signal from data</h4>
          <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
            Status is the primary signal. Details are secondary. Visual hierarchy and state-driven indicators ensure users can scan quickly and drill down when needed.
          </p>
        </section>
      </ScrollReveal>

      <!-- Key Design Decisions -->
      <ScrollReveal client:visible>
        <section>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-text-primary mt-16 mb-6">Key Design Decisions</h3>
          <ol class="list-decimal list-inside text-text-secondary space-y-2">
            <li><strong class="text-text-primary">"Completed" vs "Achieved"</strong> — Completed means confirmed via data. Achieved means inferred. This distinction exposes system confidence to the user rather than hiding uncertainty.</li>
            <li><strong class="text-text-primary">Don't overload rows</strong> — Avoid mini dashboards inside table rows. Keep rows scannable and use progressive disclosure for details.</li>
            <li><strong class="text-text-primary">Filters over columns</strong> — Columns scale badly as information grows. Filters scale well and give users control over what they see.</li>
            <li><strong class="text-text-primary">Align system and UI</strong> — Geofence events, gate-in/out timestamps, and system signals must map directly to what the UI shows. The UI reflects system truth.</li>
          </ol>
        </section>
      </ScrollReveal>

      <!-- Example Flow -->
      <ScrollReveal client:visible>
        <section>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-text-primary mt-16 mb-6">Example Flow</h3>
          <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
            <strong class="text-text-primary">User goal:</strong> Find delayed journeys.
          </p>

          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
            <div class="bg-bg-card border border-border-subtle rounded-lg p-5">
              <p class="text-text-tertiary text-xs uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">Before</p>
              <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed">
                Scan entire table, check columns one by one, no delay indicator present. Manual effort with no clear outcome.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-bg-card border border-border-subtle rounded-lg p-5">
              <p class="text-text-tertiary text-xs uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">After</p>
              <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed">
                Apply "Delayed" filter, view only relevant journeys, take immediate action. Clear path from intent to outcome.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>
      </ScrollReveal>

      <!-- What Changed -->
      <ScrollReveal client:visible>
        <section>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-text-primary mt-16 mb-6">What Changed</h3>
          <div class="overflow-x-auto">
            <table class="w-full bg-bg-card rounded border border-border-subtle text-sm">
              <thead>
                <tr class="bg-bg-secondary">
                  <th class="text-left px-4 py-3 text-text-primary font-medium border-b border-border-subtle">Before</th>
                  <th class="text-left px-4 py-3 text-text-primary font-medium border-b border-border-subtle">After</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody class="text-text-secondary">
                <tr class="border-b border-border-subtle">
                  <td class="px-4 py-3">Data-heavy</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3">Actionable</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-b border-border-subtle">
                  <td class="px-4 py-3">Reactive</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3">Prioritized</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3">Confusing states</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3">Clear lifecycle</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
        </section>
      </ScrollReveal>

      <!-- Impact -->
      <ScrollReveal client:visible>
        <section>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-text-primary mt-16 mb-6">Impact</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-text-secondary space-y-2">
            <li>Expected reduction in time to identify delayed journeys</li>
            <li>Increase in actions taken per session</li>
            <li>Reduced dependency on manual tracking workflows</li>
          </ul>
        </section>
      </ScrollReveal>

      <!-- Learnings -->
      <ScrollReveal client:visible>
        <section>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-text-primary mt-16 mb-6">Learnings</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-text-secondary space-y-2">
            <li>Tables are decision systems, not just data displays.</li>
            <li>Without a clear mental model, UI complexity grows uncontrollably and the interface degrades over time.</li>
            <li>B2B users want clarity and control, not more data.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>
      </ScrollReveal>

      <!-- What's Next -->
      <ScrollReveal client:visible>
        <section class="mb-16">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-text-primary mt-16 mb-6">What's Next</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-text-secondary space-y-2">
            <li>Build an alerting system for proactive delay notifications</li>
            <li>Predict delays from historical data patterns</li>
            <li>Personalize journey views by user role and priorities</li>
          </ul>
        </section>
      </ScrollReveal>

    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
